cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Network Latency and Energy Consumption Measurements with a Load Generation
  Workload
abstract: This dataset documents an experiment measuring network latency and energy
  consumption during workload execution. A load generation tool, MoonGen, was configured
  and used to transmit packets between nodes at varying rates and sizes. The methodology
  involved synchronizing nodes, recording energy measurements, executing the load
  generator, and capturing latency data as a histogram. Per-run logs and evaluation
  outputs are included alongside the collected measurement artifacts.
